Note:
Cross-module struct return target for
tests/compiler/stage1/test_cross_module_struct_return.runa. Declares a
Lab type and a lab_black constructor that returns a Lab struct.

A second struct type LabAlt is declared with overlapping field name 'l'
to ensure the regression test reproduces the original failure mode --
ambiguous-field dispatch in codegen_find_struct_type_for_field's Pass 2.
The fix relies on codegen_get_expression_type returning the EXPR_QUALIFIED_CALL
return type accurately, so the variable's declared type is "Lab" rather than
the default "Integer" placeholder. Pass 1's declared-type lookup then
resolves the field cleanly.
:End Note

Type called "Lab":
    l as Integer
    a as Integer
    b as Integer
End Type

Type called "LabAlt":
    l as Integer
End Type

Process called "lab_black" returns Lab:
    Let result be a value of type Lab
    Set result.l to 42
    Set result.a to 128
    Set result.b to 128
    Return result
End Process
